Two bodies were found at a dumping site in Mpumalanga on Wednesday. The bodies, with head injuries and stab wounds, were discovered by a resident at the Mogonong dumping site next to a cemetery in Siyabuswa. The community member alerted police after noticing the bodies in the rubbish, said police spokesperson Brig Selvy Mohlala. “On arrival, police noticed the  bodies of the two men and the first victim, who is dark in complexion, reportedly sustained head injuries and  scratches on his body,” Mohlala said. One man is estimated to be aged between 20 and 30 years. He was wearing blue jeans and a white T-shirt. The second victim is also dark and estimated to be aged between 30 and 40 years. He was  wearing black shorts and a grey T-shirt, Mohlala said. “His body shows  he was  stabbed with a sharp object on his throat, with minor bruises on his body.” Provincial police commissioner Lt-Gen Semakaleng Daphney Manamela said a dedicated  team of experts will investigate the deaths. “ TimesLIVE